rsPppMIB.name: rsPppMIB

revisions.description: Additional objects added to support remote access capabilities, including termination reason, authentication protocol, option negotiation status.
Initial version of this MIB module.

rsPppMIB.contactinfo: Redstone Communications, Inc. 5 Carlisle Road Westford MA 01886 USA Tel: +1-978-692-1999 Email: mib@redstonecom.com
rsPppMIB.description: The PPP MIB for the Redstone Communications Inc. enterprise.

RsPppAuthentication.name: RsPppAuthentication
RsPppAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of PPP authentication used, if any: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP.

rsPppLinkStatusTable.name: rsPppLinkStatusTable
rsPppLinkStatusTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

rsPppLinkStatusEntry.name: rsPppLinkStatusEntry
rsPppLinkStatusEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface.

rsPppLinkStatusTerminateReason.name: rsPppLinkStatusTerminateReason
rsPppLinkStatusTerminateReason.description: Reason the PPP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. adminDisable Interface administratively disabled. lowerLayerDown Underlying interface is down. noUpperInterface No interface above PPP. authenticationFailure Authentication failed. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate LCP option. See rsPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption. keepaliveFailure Keepalive failed. sessionTimeout Maximum session period expired. inactivityTimeout Maximum inactivity period expired. addressLeaseExpired Lease for network address expired. adminLogout Session administratively terminated.

rsPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption.name: rsPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption
rsPppLinkStatusTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP LCP option for which negotiation failed, when rsPppLinkStatusTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

rsPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber.name: rsPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber
rsPppLinkStatusLocalMagicNumber.description: Magic number negotiated for the local side.

rsPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber.name: rsPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber
rsPppLinkStatusRemoteMagicNumber.description: Magic number negotiated for the remote side.

rsPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication.name: rsPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication
rsPppLinkStatusLocalAuthentication.description: Authentication protocol negotiated for the local side.

rsPppLinkConfigTable.name: rsPppLinkConfigTable
rsPppLinkConfigTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

rsPppLinkConfigEntry.name: rsPppLinkConfigEntry
rsPppLinkConfigEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface. Creating/deleting entries in this table causes corresponding entries for be created /deleted in ifTable/ifXTable/rsIfTable.

rsPppLinkConfigIfIndex.name: rsPppLinkConfigIfIndex
rsPppLinkConfigIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the PPP interface. When creating entries in this table, suitable values for this object are determined by reading rsPppNextIfIndex.

rsPppLinkConfigRowStatus.name: rsPppLinkConfigRowStatus
rsPppLinkConfigRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of entries in this table according to the RowStatus textual convention, constrained to support the following values only: createAndGo destroy To create an entry in this table, the following entry objects MUST be explicitly configured: rsPppLinkConfigRowStatus rsPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex In addition, when creating an entry the following conditions must hold: A value for rsPppLinkConfigIndex must have been determined previously, by reading rsPppNextIfIndex. The interface identified by rsPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex must exist. A corresponding entry in ifTable/ifXTable/rsIfTable is created/destroyed as a result of creating/destroying an entry in this table.

rsPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.name: rsPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex
rsPppLinkConfigLowerIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of an interface over which this PPP interface is to be layered. A value of zero indicates no layering. An implementation may choose to require that a nonzero value be configured at entry creation.

rsPppLinkConfigKeepalive.name: rsPppLinkConfigKeepalive
rsPppLinkConfigKeepalive.description: Keepalive interval in seconds. A value of zero disables keepalive. Keepalive is performed using LCP Echo.

rsPppLinkConfigAuthentication.name: rsPppLinkConfigAuthentication
rsPppLinkConfigAuthentication.description: Specifies the type(s) of authentication, if any, to be negotiated with the peer: none No authentication is negotiated. pap PAP negotiation only. chap CHAP negotiation only. papChap PAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt CHAP. chapPap CHAP negotiation is attempted first; if fails, attempt PAP.

rsPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.name: rsPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries
rsPppLinkConfigMaxAuthenRetries.description: The number of authentication retries permitted, in addition to a failed initial attempt. If all retries fail, the link is reset.

rsPppNextIfIndex.name: rsPppNextIfIndex
rsPppNextIfIndex.description: Coordinate ifIndex value allocation for entries in rsPppLinkConfigTable. A GET of this object returns the next available ifIndex value to be used to create an entry in the associated interface table; or zero, if no valid ifIndex value is available. This object also returns a value of zero when it is the lexicographic successor of a varbind presented in an SNMP GETNEXT or GETBULK request, for which circumstance it is assumed that ifIndex allocation is unintended. Successive GETs will typically return different values, thus avoiding collisions among cooperating management clients seeking to create table entries simultaneously.

rsPppIpTable.name: rsPppIpTable
rsPppIpTable.description: Table containing the IP parameters for the local PPP entity.

rsPppIpEntry.name: rsPppIpEntry
rsPppIpEntry.description: IPCP status information for a particular PPP link.

rsPppIpServiceStatus.name: rsPppIpServiceStatus
rsPppIpServiceStatus.description: Indicates whether IP protocol service is operating over this PPP link. Service is established on this link through means outside this MIB.

rsPppIpTerminateReason.name: rsPppIpTerminateReason
rsPppIpTerminateReason.description: Reason the IPCP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. noService No IP service configured on this PPP link. admin Administratively disabled. linkDown Underlying link is down. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate IPCP option. See rsPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.

rsPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.name: rsPppIpTerminateNegFailOption
rsPppIpTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP IPCP option for which negotiation failed, when rsPppIpTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

rsPppIpLocalIpAddress.name: rsPppIpLocalIpAddress
rsPppIpLocalIpAddress.description: IP Address used by the local side.

rsPppIpRemoteIpAddress.name: rsPppIpRemoteIpAddress
rsPppIpRemoteIpAddress.description: IP Address used by the remote side.

rsPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.name: rsPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress
rsPppIpRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.description: Primary DNS server used by the remote side.

rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.name: rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress
rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.description: Secondary DNS server used by the remote side.

rsPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.name: rsPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress
rsPppIpRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.description: Primary WINS server used by the remote side.

rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.name: rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress
rsPppIpRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.description: Secondary WINS server used by the remote side.

rsPppIpConfigTable.name: rsPppIpConfigTable
rsPppIpConfigTable.description: Table containing the IP parameters for the local PPP entity.

rsPppIpConfigEntry.name: rsPppIpConfigEntry
rsPppIpConfigEntry.description: IPCP configuration information for a particular PPP link.

rsPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority.name: rsPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority
rsPppIpConfigPeerDnsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's DNS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's DNS address prevails.

rsPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority.name: rsPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority
rsPppIpConfigPeerWinsPriority.description: When enabled, allows peer's WINS address to prevail in the event of a negotiation conflict; when disabled, the local PPP interface's WINS address prevails.

rsPppOsiTable.name: rsPppOsiTable
rsPppOsiTable.description: Table containing the OSI parameters for the local PPP entity.

rsPppOsiEntry.name: rsPppOsiEntry
rsPppOsiEntry.description: OSICP status information for a particular PPP link.

rsPppOsiServiceStatus.name: rsPppOsiServiceStatus
rsPppOsiServiceStatus.description: Indicates whether OSI protocol service is operating over this PPP link. Service is established on this link through means outside this MIB.

rsPppOsiOperStatus.name: rsPppOsiOperStatus
rsPppOsiOperStatus.description: The operational status of the OSI network protocol. If the value of this object is up then the finite state machine for the OSI network protocol has reached the Opened state.

rsPppOsiTerminateReason.name: rsPppOsiTerminateReason
rsPppOsiTerminateReason.description: Reason the OSICP link was terminated: none None. other Not specified. noService No OSI service configured on this PPP link. admin Administratively disabled. linkDown Underlying link is down. peerTerminated Peer initiated termination. peerRenegotiated Peer initiated renegotiation. maxRetriesExceeded Maximum number of config retries exceeded. negotiationFailure Failed to negotiate IPCP option. See rsPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.

rsPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.name: rsPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption
rsPppOsiTerminateNegFailOption.description: Reports the PPP OSICP option for which negotiation failed, when rsPppOsiTerminateReason has the value 'negotiationFailure'.

rsPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu.name: rsPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu
rsPppOsiLocalAlignNpdu.description: Local alignment of network PDU: none No alignment specified. oneModulo4 Alignment on first octet (out of four). twoModulo4 Alignment on second octet (out of four). threeModulo4 Alignment on third octet (out of four). fourModulo4 Alignment on fourth octet (out of four). even Alignment on even-octet boundary. odd Alignment on odd-octet boundary.

rsPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu.name: rsPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu
rsPppOsiRemoteAlignNpdu.description: Remote alignment of network PDU. none No alignment specified. oneModulo4 Alignment on first octet (out of four). twoModulo4 Alignment on second octet (out of four). threeModulo4 Alignment on third octet (out of four). fourModulo4 Alignment on fourth octet (out of four). even Alignment on even-octet boundary. odd Alignment on odd-octet boundary.

rsPppOsiConfigTable.name: rsPppOsiConfigTable
rsPppOsiConfigTable.description: Table containing configuration variables for the OSICP for the local PPP entity.

rsPppOsiConfigEntry.name: rsPppOsiConfigEntry
rsPppOsiConfigEntry.description: OSICP information for a particular PPP link.

rsPppOsiConfigAdminStatus.name: rsPppOsiConfigAdminStatus
rsPppOsiConfigAdminStatus.description: The immediate desired status of the OSI network protocol. Setting this object to open will inject an administrative open event into the OSI network protocol's finite state machine. Setting this object to close will inject an administrative close event into the OSI network protocol's finite state machine.

rsPppSessionTable.name: rsPppSessionTable
rsPppSessionTable.description: This table contains entries for PPP interfaces present in the system.

rsPppSessionEntry.name: rsPppSessionEntry
rsPppSessionEntry.description: Each entry describes the characteristics of a PPP interface.

rsPppSessionGrant.name: rsPppSessionGrant
rsPppSessionGrant.description: Indicates whether a session has been granted via the authentication mechanism.

rsPppSessionTerminateReason.name: rsPppSessionTerminateReason
rsPppSessionTerminateReason.description: The reason the session was terminated.

rsPppSessionStartTime.name: rsPppSessionStartTime
rsPppSessionStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this session last became active.

rsPppSessionInOctets.name: rsPppSessionInOctets
rsPppSessionInOctets.description: Number of octets received since this session last became active, as denoted by rsPppSessionStartTime.

rsPppSessionOutOctets.name: rsPppSessionOutOctets

rsPppSessionInPackets.name: rsPppSessionInPackets
rsPppSessionInPackets.description: Number of packets received since this session last became active, as denoted by rsPppSessionStartTime.

rsPppSessionOutPackets.name: rsPppSessionOutPackets
rsPppSessionOutPackets.description: Number of packets sent since this session last became active, as denoted by rsPppSessionStartTime.

rsPppSessionSessionTimeout.name: rsPppSessionSessionTimeout
rsPppSessionSessionTimeout.description: Maximum duration for the session, after which the session terminates automatically.

rsPppSessionInactivityTimeout.name: rsPppSessionInactivityTimeout
rsPppSessionInactivityTimeout.description: Maximum inactivity duration for the session, after which the session terminates automatically.

rsPppSessionAccountingInterval.name: rsPppSessionAccountingInterval
rsPppSessionAccountingInterval.description: Interval that must elapse between generation of accounting records for this session.

rsPppSessionRemoteIpAddress.name: rsPppSessionRemoteIpAddress
rsPppSessionRemoteIpAddress.description: Remote IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

rsPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.name: rsPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress
rsPppSessionRemotePrimaryDnsAddress.description: Remote primary DNS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.name: rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress
rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryDnsAddress.description: Remote secondary DNS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.

rsPppSessionRemotePrimaryWinsAddress.name: rsPppSessionRemotePrimaryWinsAddress

rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.name: rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress
rsPppSessionRemoteSecondaryWinsAddress.description: Remote secondary WINS IP address, obtained from the authentication service, to be used during IPCP negotiation with the remote side.
